EWETOOB! Welcome to my channel, where every Thursday I do everything from comedy sketches to songs, vlogs, cartoons, and collaborations with sexy people.

'Twas the night before Apocalypse, when all through the house
I nervously paced and unbuttoned my blouse.
My stockings were pulled up each leg with much care,
And I'd teased, curled and sprayed every lock of my hair.

The girls were nestled all snug in their beds,
I'd had no carbohydrates- no rice and no breads.
But vodka doesn't count, so I poured a nightcap.
Probably had a bit much 'cause it dropped in my lap.

When out in the street there arose such a clatter,
That I reached for the door- Hey, I swear I look fatter!
Oh well, such is life.  So I gave one last flash,
Then forgot I had promised to take out the trash.

It's freaking L.A. Why's it feel like there's snow?
I could put on a jacket, but my outfit would blow.
When, what to my nearsighted eyes should appear?
It must be an asteroid!  Apocalypse is here!

I have many regrets, better do something quick!
I'll text my ex-boyfriend and call him a-
There's that one Christmas party where nobody came,
And that small structure fire caused by one tiny flame.

Well if this is the end, at least I look like a vixen.
I had a great life and I sure got my kicks in.
I'll set down my burdens and I'll sit on this wall,
And enjoy my last moments as the world starts to fall.

The $%*#?!  Nothing happened.  That's not how this works!
Those freaking Mayans, what a bunch of jerks!
I got myself dressed up and powdered my nose,
Then stood in the cold and I basically froze.

I'll head back inside. Did someone just whistle?
It looks like he's holding a toe made of mistle.
I should really get contacts, I have such poor sight.
Holy crap, it's Santa!  Gonna be a gooooooood night!
